## 2.1.0 (2026-03-16)

### GitHub Issue Model v2 — Phase-Level Tracking + Roadmap Planning
[New] type:initiative and type:release labels in label taxonomy
[New] Target Date field (DATE) in ecosystem project setup
[New] Initiative issue type for roadmap planning (directional time-boxed)
[New] Release issue type for versioned release tracking
[New] Two-horizon roadmap: Planning Roadmap (Target Date) + Execution Roadmap (Release)
[New] Diagram 9: Issue Hierarchy (initiative → release → phase → comments)
[New] Diagram 10: Two-Horizon Roadmap visualization
[Change] Issue tracking granularity from per-task to per-phase (~72% API call reduction)
[Change] Task progress tracked via phase issue comments, not separate issues
[Change] mgr command: phase-level issue management, initiative awareness
[Change] sys-eng command: task-completion comments, phase issue commit refs
[Change] sys-qa command: QA verdict comments on phase issues
[Change] sys-sentinel agent: findings posted as phase issue comments
[Change] refresh command: removed task issue sync, added initiative/release sync
[Change] rel-prep/rel-ship/rel-merge: type:release labels, initiative lifecycle
[Change] ecosystem-init: idempotent field updates, DATE type support
[Change] README, RDF.md, WORKFORCE.md, diagrams updated for v2 model
[Change] Core governance: issue conventions rewritten for v2

